The Los Angeles police have said that five persons have been arrested in connection to the fatal shooting of rapper, Pop Smoke during a home invasion in February. The Los Angeles Police Department in a tweet via its official Twitter account on Thursday said that three adult males and two juvenile males have been taken into custody. The Police also said that multiple people were in the home when the shooting took place. Recall that the popular 20-year-old New York rapper was killed at his home in Hollywood, Los Angeles. It was also learned that the rapper was attacked after two men wearing hoodies and masks entered the house and fired multiple shots. However, he was taken to a hospital in West Hollywood where he was pronounced dead.  